<p>The <code>now</code> function returns the current Unix timestamp.</p>

<h2>Basic Usage</h2>
<pre>{open}now{close}</pre>
<p>Timestamp: <b>{now}</b></p>

<h2>Format Current Time</h2>
<pre>{open}echo {open}now{close} | date('Y-m-d'){close}</pre>
<p>Today: <b>{echo {now} | date('Y-m-d')}</b></p>

<h2>Full DateTime</h2>
<pre>{open}echo {open}now{close} | date('Y-m-d H:i:s'){close}</pre>
<p>Now: <b>{echo {now} | date('Y-m-d H:i:s')}</b></p>

<h2>Chained Examples</h2>
<pre>{open}echo {open}now{close} | date('l, F j, Y'){close}</pre>
<p>Full date: <b>{echo {now} | date('l, F j, Y')}</b></p>

<pre>{open}echo {open}now{close} | date('H:i'){close}</pre>
<p>Time: <b>{echo {now} | date('H:i')}</b></p>

<h2>Note</h2>
<p>Returns Unix timestamp (seconds since 1970-01-01). Pipe to <code>date</code> for formatting.</p>
